## Required by security review [FUL-2988](/FUL/issues/FUL-2988)

Security Lead reviewed PR #28 (admin auth middleware) and found two code-level security issues that must be fixed before the PR can be approved.

---

### Fix 1 — Non-constant-time secret comparison

Both `middleware.ts` and `app/api/admin/login/route.ts` use `===` to compare secrets. JavaScript `===` is not constant-time; the login endpoint in particular is exposed to timing-based password enumeration.

**Files:** `middleware.ts:16`, `app/api/admin/login/route.ts:17`

**Required change:** Add a `safeCompare` helper using `crypto.timingSafeEqual`:

```ts
import { timingSafeEqual } from "crypto";

function safeCompare(a: string, b: string): boolean {
  const bufA = Buffer.from(a);
  const bufB = Buffer.from(b);
  if (bufA.length !== bufB.length) return false;
  return timingSafeEqual(bufA, bufB);
}
```

Use `safeCompare(cookie.value, secret)` in `isAdminAuthenticated()` and `safeCompare(password, secret)` in the login route POST handler.

---

### Fix 2 — Path-traversal bypass in `next` param sanitization

**File:** `app/api/admin/login/route.ts:21-22`

