## Problem

When an issue transitions to `done`, the active heartbeat run (LLM process) is NOT terminated. Only `cancelled` status kills the run:

```typescript
// server/src/routes/issues.ts
const shouldCancelActiveRunForCancelledStatus =
  existing.status !== "cancelled" && updateFields.status === "cancelled";
```

This causes the UI to display the agent as "still working/streaming" even after the issue is already `done` in the backend. This is the root cause of the observation in [FUL-4017](/FUL/issues/FUL-4017) (FUL-4013 appeared to still be running while done).

## Required Fix

Extend the run-cancellation logic to cover `done` as well as `cancelled`:

```typescript
// Before:
const shouldCancelActiveRunForCancelledStatus =
  existing.status !== "cancelled" && updateFields.status === "cancelled";

// After:
const shouldCancelActiveRunForTerminalStatus =
  !["done", "cancelled"].includes(existing.status) &&
  ["done", "cancelled"].includes(updateFields.status ?? "");
```

Update all downstream references from `shouldCancelActiveRunForCancelledStatus` → `shouldCancelActiveRunForTerminalStatus`.

